National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan, along with other members of the National Security Council, will be visiting Brazil and Argentina. The purpose of the trip is to meet with leaders of the Major Non-NATO allies in the Americas and discuss various topics such as strengthening the U.S.-Brazil strategic partnership, regional stability, climate objectives, digital infrastructure collaboration, and COVID-19 pandemic recovery. In Argentina, they will focus on increasing strategic ties, pandemic recovery, the regional climate summit, and economic growth and security in the hemisphere and globally.